Using the Central Limit Theorem, \(\bar{X}\) is approximately normally distributed. The probability \(P(0.5 \leq \bar{X} \leq \frac{2}{3})\) is standardized using \(Z = \frac{\bar{X} - 0.5}{1/12}\):

