Problem: 6.3-5. Let $Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8$ be the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous-type distribution with 70 th percentile $\pi_{0.7}=27.3$.
(a) Determine $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$.
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: The probability \( P(Y_7 < 27.3) \) is determined using the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous distribution with the 70th percentile \( \pi_{0.7} = 27.3 \). This implies that \( P(X \leq 27.3) = 0.7 \) for any random variable \( X \) from this distribution. Since the distribution is continuous, \( P(Y_7 \leq 27.3) = P(Y_7 < 27.3) \).

The event \( \{Y_7 \leq 27.3\} \) occurs if at least 7 of the 8 observations are less than or equal to 27.3. The number of observations \( S \) less than or equal to 27.3 follows a binomial distribution with parameters \( n = 8 \) and \( p = 0.7 \). Thus,
\[
P(Y_7 \leq 27.3) = P(S \geq 7) = P(S = 7) + P(S = 8).
\]

Calculate each term:
\[
P(S = 7) = \binom{8}{7} (0.7)^7 (0.3) = 8 \times (0.7)^7 \times 0.3,
\]
\[
(0.7)^7 = 0.0823543, \quad \text{so} \quad 8 \times 0.0823543 \times 0.3 = 0.19765032.
\]
\[
P(S = 8) = \binom{8}{8} (0.7)^8 = (0.7)^8 = 0.05764801.
\]
Summing these:
\[
P(S \geq 7) = 0.19765032 + 0.05764801 = 0.25529833.
\]

Rounding 0.25529833 to three significant figures gives 0.255. The value is a probability and has no unit.

