Solution: The problem involves finding the probability that the fourth white ball is drawn on the fourth draw when sampling with replacement from an urn containing 10 red and 10 white balls. With replacement, the probability of drawing a white ball on any single draw is \( \frac{10}{20} = 0.5 \).

