* N: 1 *
********
**************
* RESPONSE 1 *
**************
The solution calculates the conditional probability that an offspring has two white alleles given that it has white eyes. The genotypes resulting in white eyes are RW, WR, or WW, with a total probability of \( \frac{3}{4} \). The probability of the WW genotype is \( \frac{1}{4} \). The conditional probability is \( P(\text{WW} \mid \text{white}) = \frac{P(\text{WW and white})}{P(\text{white})} = \frac{\frac{1}{4}}{\frac{3}{4}} = \frac{1}{3} \). This is approximated as 0.333 when rounded to three significant figures.

