- The probability that at least one ball is orange is \( 1 - \frac{\binom{2}{2}}{\binom{4}{2}} = 1 - \frac{1}{6} = \frac{5}{6} \).
- The conditional probability is \( \frac{\frac{1}{6}}{\frac{5}{6}} = \frac{1}{5} = 0.2 \).

